\n<Female>The name of this town is "Drine." It means sinkhole. It was
formed when the ground suddenly collapsed, creating a hole.
This town was built inside that hole.

\n<Female>Above this town live the upper class, and we commoners like
us live off the scraps they throw down.

\n<Female>This is where those who have lost their way end up,
swallowed up like into a drain. All sorts of schemes and
desires swirl around here.

\n<Female>It seems you have a pass to Lumare. Seeing the difference
between the lower and upper areas, I wonder what goes
through your mind.

\n<Female>It seems that Ladro-chan has gone missing. Well,
disappearances are common in this town... but for someone to
vanish from the orphanage of all places.

\n<Female>I'm not exactly in a position to offer much help myself...
but it's just so pitiful.

\n<Female>If you have the means, please consider stopping by the
orphanage or giving donations and food.

\n<Grandpa>It's tough going up and down since we're staying in the
noble district. It's quite harsh on an old body like mine.

\n<Grandpa>The head of the family is furious. If they find out I've
been turning a blind eye like this, I might lose my head.
Please persuade them if that happens.

\n<Grandpa>Right now, everyone in the mansion is looking for you two.
Well, they'd never imagine you're in Dri-Ne, so there's no
worry of being found.

\n<Grandpa>How did I know you were here? Well, as your tutor, I can see
right through both of your thoughts.

\n<Grandpa>But my body can't keep up anymore... It took quite some time
to get here. It took about six days by carriage, with plenty
of rest.

\n<Grandpa>I'm well-versed in self-defense, so it's no problem if I'm

\n<Grandpa>I won't enter the Adventurer's Guild. It would be
troublesome if your identities were questioned. I'll just
loiter around here.
